      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh sensitivity study — impeller passage refinement",
      "description": "Three-level mesh refinement study on impeller passage geometry. GCI values reported for wall shear stress and hemolysis index at nominal operating point. Structured UQ node links discretisation error estimates to validation activity.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/gci-mesh-sensitivity-vad"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-cou2-off-design",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Off-design operating condition — qualitative variability assessment",
      "description": "Validation at the extreme low-flow off-design condition (2 L/min, 4500 rpm). Experimental replicates showed elevated run-to-run scatter attributed to inlet flow instabilities; inherent variability assessed qualitatively by the test engineer based on visual inspection of replicate pressure-rise curves. No structured Monte Carlo or interval-based UQ node was generated for this result. The qualitative assessment notes that variability is expected to be bounded but this characterisation is not formalised in the evidence package."
    }
